Vice President Biden expresses gratitude to General Jim Jones for his service to the administration and the nation, commending his steady hand, sound judgment, and genuine decency. Jones did not actively seek the position he is leaving, but answered the call to service. Vice President Biden also highlights the friendship and advisory role of Tom Donilon, who has been at the center of foreign and national security policies for the past two years. Donilon's extensive knowledge about global challenges and opportunities makes him a valuable asset in his new responsibilities. President Obama and Vice President Biden appreciate his counsel and leadership.